summary: SummaryIT Cosmetics Superhero Volumizing Waterproof Mascara gives your eyelashes super volume, length and elastic stretch with up to 24HR wear, no flaking or smudging.
details: DetailsFeaturesGive your eyelashes Superhero powers with Superhero Waterproof Mascara, a lash-plumping, lengthening and volumizing mascara that provides 20x more volume and 41% more visible length vs. your natural lashes.With its life-proof formula, this buildable and long-lasting mascara resists smudging, sweat, flaking and humidity while still feeling comfortable on your lashes.The lash-loving biotin, peptides and pro-vitamin B5 coat lashes from root to tip while the Lash Changing Power Brush brings the drama to lift and separate.Developed with plastic surgeons' insights and dermatologists’ ingredient and skincare expertise, IT Cosmetics creates problem-solving, skin-loving formulas that give you visible results.BenefitsVolumizing waterproof mascara for super volume, length and elastic stretch in one coat!Life-proof formula: resists smudging, sweat, flaking and humidity24HR & waterproof wear20x more volume & 41% more visible length vs. your natural lashesLife-proof Lash Armor coats lashes in a flexible layer to resist water, humidity, and sweat without a crunchy feel.Real Results: - 92% say it's buildable* - 90% say it provides big volume* - 90% say it feels comfortable on lashes* - *Results observed in a consumer panel surveyKey IngredientsPro-Vitamin B5: Known for its lash-conditioning benefitsPeptides: Helps brittle lashes look softBiotin: Vitamin that promotes healthier-looking hair and skinItem 2606740How To UseStarting at the base of your eyelashes, wiggle and sweep up and through to the tips. You'll see dramatic eye makeup results in just one coat! Apply additional coats if desired. Remove with an oil-based makeup remover or cleanser, such as IT Cosmetics Bye Bye Makeup 3-in-1 Makeup Melting Cleansing Balm.IngredientsAqua / Water / Eau, Isododecane, Synthetic Beeswax, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Polyacrylate-21, Copernicia Cerifera Cera / Carnauba Wax / Cire De Carnauba, Isononyl Isononanoate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, C30-45 Alkyldimethylsilyl, Polypropylsilsesquioxane, Dimethicone, Peg-30 Dipolyhydroxystearate, Propylene Glycol, Peg-10 Dimethicone, Bis-Peg-12 Dimethicone Beeswax, Candelilla Cera / Candelilla Wax / Cire De Candelilla, Phenoxyethanol, Lauryl Peg-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Caprylyl Glycol, Magnesium Sulfate, Butylene Glycol, Benzoic Acid, Trideceth-6 Phosphate, Biotin, Dipropylene Glycol, Glyceryl Caprylate, Panthenol, Glycerin, Tocopherol, Steareth-20, Chlorhexidine Digluconate, N-Hydroxysuccinimide, Sodium Citrate, Potassium Sorbate, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1, Chrysin, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7, Citric Acid, [+/- May Contain / Peut Contenir CI 77499 / Iron Oxides].Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

Remove with an oil-based makeup remover or cleanser, such as IT Cosmetics Bye Bye Makeup 3-in-1 Makeup Melting Cleansing Balm.

reviews.headline: Great mascara!
reviews.comments: Easy to use and doesn't clump.

reviews.headline: Okay….ish
reviews.comments: I haven't gone out and replaced it with a new tube of another brand just yet, but I do not like the clumping.

reviews.headline: I wanted to like it
reviews.comments: I wanted to love this mascara but it was too clumpy. This mascara made my lashes weigh down. It's not light weight and doesn't curl my lashes. Wouldn't recommend it

reviews.headline: Would definitely buy again
reviews.comments: This mascara is thick but not pasty. It extends my lashes and leaves them looking flawless

reviews.headline: Best WP out there
reviews.comments: I wear TWO contacts in 1 eye,scleral in the other. PLUS- live in balmy humid Florida. Also an ICU nurse, lots of long shifts, tears, sweat ,rain,&  humidity.. & hot flashes;‐).  I've tried everything from Dior to Lancome. Those are both close Runners up but this one is my new favorite..

reviews.headline: Smudge central
reviews.comments: Have had to wipe eyelid and undereye of smudges over and over again. Havent even gotten wet yet. Barely looks like I have more to an a tint and clumped and pulled off when trying to layer

reviews.headline: It's an "on sale" only mascara
reviews.comments: I like the wand, but it feels kind of thick. Lengthened, but was a little clumpy. Made my lashes look fluffy, but transferred. I bought it during the summer sale, and it might still go back.

reviews.headline: Do not buy
reviews.comments: Looks like you have no mascara on pretty much. I love the regular super hero mascara not even close to the same results. Bummer I love IT cosmetics this was the first mascara I ever returned in my life.

reviews.headline: I would not buy again
reviews.comments: Goes on to clumpy for my eyelashes

reviews.headline: Heavy
reviews.comments: If you have straight lashes this is not it. Way too heavy, straightened my lashes at the first coat.

reviews.headline: I will not buy this product again.
reviews.comments: Too thick and heavy.

reviews.headline: Not good
reviews.comments: Mascara is to wet. Brings my lashes down and looks as if I am wearing nothing. I will return.

reviews.headline: NOT water proof
reviews.comments: The instant my skin was moist, from a typical workday, there were shadows beneath my eyes.  I wasn't sweating, just a little heated.  Not worth the money at all!!

reviews.headline: what kind of "waterproof" mascara is this?
reviews.comments: I have quite literally never used a mascara that is this bad. First, it states that it's waterproof but that could not be any further from the truth. It runs SO bad. Within an hour I have mascara smudges under my eye and at the top of my eyelid, so I am constantly having to clean up the marks. My non-waterproof mascaras dont even run this bad. Second, it clumps horribly. My eyelashes look like spider legs instead of individual lashes. I got this for free with my platinum gift at rhe beginning of the year, so I am glad I did not actually spend money this. I do NOT recommend this mascara at all.

reviews.headline: Not the best
reviews.comments: I wasn't fond of this mascara after buying it, I've worn it a few times now. I don't recommend if you have sensitive eyes, it will irritate them the next day; it is extremely hard to remove even with makeup remover.

reviews.headline: Another one bites the dust
reviews.comments: From the very first use, was clumpy, didnt apply without making gaps in my lashes. I should have returned but wanted to give it a try. Never again!

reviews.headline: Nope
reviews.comments: I used to love this mascara and every time it will go on sale i would stock up, so i dont know if ulta is selling old ones or IT downgraded the formula in order to sell the primer, i havent tried the primer as i consider the mascara to be pricey already, its not like i can add more cost on my already tight budget.

reviews.headline: Brush is not good
reviews.comments: Tge brush design doesn't allow for excess mascara to be cleaned off for better application

reviews.headline: Not a keeper
reviews.comments: I will be returning this. Even though it is waterproof, it somehow managed to smudge below my eyes… which not even regular mascara has done.

reviews.headline: Beware: Transfers!
reviews.comments: Use with caution and in small amounts… it's so thick & clumpy. Definitely would *not* recommend, unless you like a smudged look.

faceoff_positive.headline: Best waterproof, mascara ever.

faceoff_negative.comments: I was disappointed by this waterproof superhero mascara. First it did not provide the near the results of the OG superhero mascara as far as length and volume. Secondly this mascara transferred to my lids throughout the day. Lastly this mascara is not waterproof. I used alittle splash of water and barely rubbed it out of my eyes and it smeared all over my face. Overall the performance of this mascara was highly disappointing.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not as good as the OG.
